                              uid=50_104 heading "LEARN BY DOING" level="3"
                                uid=50_105 StaticText "LEARN BY DOING"
                              uid=50_106 ignored
                                uid=50_107 paragraph
                                  uid=50_108 StaticText "The word "
                                  uid=50_109 strong
                                    uid=50_110 StaticText "Nido"
                                  uid=50_111 StaticText " is Italian for nest. The Nido environment focuses on the basic needs of the infant, a safe bonded relationship between the caregivers and the child, respecting each individual child and the development of the child’s increasing sense of self and independence."
                                uid=50_112 paragraph
                                  uid=50_113 StaticText "The simplicity and order of our Nido environments allow for safe exploration and discovery of the world around them.  "
                                uid=50_114 paragraph
                                  uid=50_115 StaticText "Trust is a basic need that must be nurtured in the young child. Our trained caregivers respectfully respond to the needs of each child and when doing so, this builds a relationship between the two and sends the message to the child that he is unconditionally loved and accepted."
                        uid=50_116 generic
                          uid=50_117 generic
                            uid=50_118 generic
                              uid=50_119 ignored
                                uid=50_120 paragraph
                                uid=50_121 paragraph
                                uid=50_122 paragraph
                                  uid=50_123 StaticText "In our Nido environments we believe in the freedom of movement. You will not find children constrained in contraptions, rather you will see the infant placed on their back exploring the environment around them.  They are able to move in a natural way and when they are ready. Our floor beds allow for the mobile infant to wake and move off his bed when ready.  "
                                uid=50_124 paragraph
                                  uid=50_125 StaticText "Feeding in our Nido environment is done so in a respecting way. The infant that is bottle-fed is held close and given undivided attention while drinking the bottle. The child that is sitting up on his own will sit at a small table, drink from a mini glass and eat off a real plate."
                                uid=50_126 paragraph
                                  uid=50_127 StaticText "Our infants have an outside area where they are able to get out and have fresh air and enjoy the trees and sounds of nature."
                    uid=50_128 generic
                      uid=50_129 generic
                        uid=50_130 generic
                          uid=50_131 generic
                            uid=50_132 generic
                              uid=50_133 heading "BEYOND THE BOOKS" level="3"
                                uid=50_134 StaticText "BEYOND THE BOOKS"
                              uid=50_135 ignored
                                uid=50_136 paragraph
                                  uid=50_137 StaticText "At Sundrops we strive to educate by nurturing the social, emotional and cognitive developmental needs for each student, individually. Our mission is to awaken your child’s natural desire to learn in an environment where trust, respect, responsibility, community and cooperation flourish. Our classrooms are specially prepared environments with materials that stimulate a student’s sense of curiosity and offer dynamic learning at a student’s own pace."
